A Cryptographically Secure Pseudo-Random Number Generator (CSPRNG) can be used to generate "salt".

openssl_random_pseudo_bytes is available in PHP.

Documentations source.
https://www.php.net/manual/en/function.openssl-random-pseudo-bytes.php

crypt() is a PHP funtion to hash strings.

So for every new user created we can generate a salt with the first function combine it with the user password and hash it with crypt.

Documentation source.
https://www.php.net/manual/en/function.crypt.php

